Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setObjFPlanPolygon(25.10)                            setObjFPlanPolygon(25.10)

Name
       setObjFPlanPolygon  - Specifies a rectilinear object with polygon coor-
       dinates

Syntax
        setObjFPlanPolygon

       [-help]

       {Cell | Group | Instance | Layershape | Module }

       objectName

       coordList

       [-no_snap_to_grid]

       Specifies a rectilinear object with polygon coordinates. The  rectilin-
       ear  object can take any shape depending on the number of x and y coor-
       dinates you specify. You can use this command after importing  the  de-
       sign.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each setObjFPlanPolygon parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man setObjFPlanPolygon

       <objectName>
              Specifies the name of the object.

              Data_type: string, required

              {Cell | Group | Instance | Layershape | Module}"  Specifies  the
              type of object. The object type can be:

              * Cell

              * Group

              * Instance

              * Layershape

              * Module

              Data_type: enum, required

       <coordList>
              Specifies  the  corner  coordinates, {x1 y1 x2 y2 .....}, of the
              rectilinear object. The rectilinear object can  take  any  shape
              depending on the number of x and y coordinates you specify.

              Data_type: list, required

       -no_snap_to_grid
              When specified, the snap rules are not honored and a user-speci-
              fied  object is not snapped to the grid even if it overlaps with
              the die box.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Example
       The following command defines a rectilinear object -  module  xyz  with
       five pairs of corner coordinates.

       setObjFPlanPolygon  module xyz 371.46 537.60 371.46 754.35 412.5 754.35
       412.5 920.64 696.96 920.64 696.96 537.60

Related Information
              * getObjFPlanPolygon

              * Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

